               <p>I lost a copper from my door, in <placeName id="t17900707-21-crimeloc106">Oxford-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17900707-21-crimeloc106" type="placeName" value="Oxford-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17900707-21-crimeloc106" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17900707-21-off104 t17900707-21-crimeloc106"></join>, exposed to sale; it was on Friday, the 18th of June, between five and six in the evening; I saw it within a quarter of an hour. In the course of the afternoon, the prisoner came to me, and asked me the price of a stove; I asked him three shillings and sixpence; I saw him lurking about; I bid my son watch him; and he brought him back with the copper; I did not see him take it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17900707-21-person239">
                  CHARLES
                   THORNTON
               <interp inst="t17900707-21-person239" type="surname" value="THORNTON"></interp>
